meanings.definition: To surpass in feeling or emotion.
meanings.sent1: She always seems to outfeel everyone in the room.
meanings.sent2: I outfeel my friends when it comes to watching sad movies.
meanings.sent3: At the party, she managed to outfeel even the most emotional guests.
meanings.sent4: Her love for animals outfeels her fear of spiders.
meanings.sent5: His passion for music outfeels any other hobby he has.

meanings.definition: To experience a stronger emotion than someone else.
meanings.sent1: When I see puppies, I outfeel my sister who is scared of them.
meanings.sent2: He tends to outfeel his classmates during sad scenes in movies.
meanings.sent3: Even at a young age, the child could outfeel the adults in the room.
meanings.sent4: Her excitement outfeels her nervousness before the performance.
meanings.sent5: The joy of winning outfeels the disappointment of losing.

meanings.definition: To have a greater emotional response than others.
meanings.sent1: She can outfeel her brother when it comes to expressing emotions.
meanings.sent2: During the concert, the singer outfeels the audience with her heartfelt performance.
meanings.sent3: The little girl managed to outfeel her parents with her reaction to the surprise.
meanings.sent4: His gratitude outfeels any other emotion he has ever experienced.
meanings.sent5: The beauty of the sunset outfeels the stress of the day.
